events.param: terminal LOG 170.??: I have not felt happy in a long time, but today I stood atop a gleaming little star, and thought, what a beautiful way to die.
party 0 I wish Erin could see this.
terminal LOG ???.??: We were wrong to push forward. We should have stayed. Still, there is an eerie beauty here. I feel strangely lucky.
The very fabric of reality seems to be peeling apart. The great laws of physics have clocked out for the day and left your party behind in a splintering kaleidoscope.
note NAME finds a smashed tape deck and a pair of broken headphones.
party 4 Is anyone else cold? I can't stop shivering.
terminal LOG 156.??: Found Hector. He is not the person I thought he was. He killed Patrick, so I killed him. Now I am alone here.
